text.section:
An insurance purchasing outlet shall:
Set and collect fees to finance necessary costs incurred in marketing, selling, servicing, and administering its services;
Offer health benefit plans to eligible persons;
Provide premium and voucher collection services for participating insurers;
Establish and adhere to appropriate administrative and accounting procedures for operating the health purchasing outlet;
Establish and adhere to rules, conditions, and procedures for insurance purchasing outlet members and participating insurers;
Establish and adhere to enrollment and participation requirements for insurance purchasing outlet members;
Receive, review, and conduct appeals for persons who have been denied enrollment to an insurance purchasing outlet;
Demonstrate and maintain at all times proof of financial responsibility and solvency;
Prepare an annual report on the operations of the insurance purchasing outlet in accordance with administrative regulations promulgated by the commissioner;
Establish procedures for billing and collection of premiums from insurance purchasing outlet members;
Establish procedures for collecting and redeeming vouchers; and
Maintain an administrator license in accordance with Subtitle 9 of Chapter 304.

An insurance purchasing outlet may:
Contract with qualified third parties for any services necessary to carry out the powers and duties authorized or required by this chapter;
Employ necessary staff;
Sue or be sued;
Contract with independent licensed administrators to adjust or settle claims, since the insurance purchasing outlet is prohibited from these activities in accordance with KRS 304.17A-758; and
Employ, contract, or otherwise use licensed insurance agents to market and service coverage.
